Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{2} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the macaroni.

When boiling, stir the @macaroni{180%g} into the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the macaroni cooks, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Crispy Breadcrumb Topping ==

In a small #bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{25%g} and @oil{2%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside for now.

== Cheese Sauce ==

Melt the @butter{20%g} in another large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, stir in the garlic and fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @plain flour{1.5%tbsp} into the garlic butter. Cook until it forms a paste, ~{1-2%minutes} - you've made a roux!

Pour the @water{200%ml} for the sauce into the roux a little at a time, followed by the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil, stir and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, then remove from the heat.

Add the @vegan 'nduja{1/2%sachet} and grated Cheddar to the sauce. Stir until combined and melted.

> Add less nduja if you'd prefer things milder.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

== Assembly ==

Once the sweet potato is roasted, remove it from the oven and turn your #grill{} on to high.

Stir the roasted sweet potato into the cheese sauce along with the cooked macaroni.

Transfer the pasta to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}. Sprinkle over the breadcrumbs, then pop it under the grill until golden and bubbling, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Share the mac & cheese between your plates.

Serve the @baby leaf mix{20%g} salad alongside. Drizzle the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} over the leaves to finish.

Enjoy!